customHtml.title: Casino Canberra — Excitement and Style in the Heart of Canberra
customHtml.description:
Casino Canberra is the only licensed casino in the Australian Capital Territory, located at 21 Binara Street, near Glebe Park and opposite Crowne Plaza. Since its opening in 1994, it has become a landmark destination for gaming enthusiasts, fine dining lovers, and those seeking vibrant nightlife. The casino operates daily from 12:00 PM to 4:00 AM, offering guests a comfortable atmosphere and a wide range of entertainment options.


The gaming floor features 39 tables with classic games such as Blackjack, Roulette, Baccarat, Pai Gow, Sic Bo, and Pontoon. Poker fans can enjoy regular tournaments with buy-ins starting at $115 and prize pools reaching up to $6,000. One of Casino Canberra’s unique aspects is the absence of poker machines, creating a more relaxed environment focused on traditional table games. For those who appreciate modern technology, Stadium Gaming offers electronic versions of popular games with live dealers.


Casino Canberra is not only about gaming but also about exceptional dining experiences. Onyx Sports Bar is the perfect spot to watch live sports events like UFC, Formula 1, and the Super Bowl on big screens while placing bets via TAB. Guests can enjoy Happy Hour with discounted drinks. Main Bar serves cocktails, wine, and beer, while the on-site restaurant offers a mix of Japanese, Indian, Vietnamese, and Australian dishes.


For visitors planning an extended stay, nearby accommodations include Crowne Plaza Canberra, QT Canberra, and Hotel Realm. The casino is also known for its vibrant events calendar, featuring live music on weekends, themed shows, wine dinners, and sports nights. In the past, the venue hosted the retro-style Galaxy Club, and today the schedule includes burlesque performances and culinary festivals.


Those seeking big wins will appreciate tournaments in Blackjack, Roulette, and Baccarat with prize pools up to $3,000, as well as poker events offering payouts up to $6,000. Minimum bets start at $5, while maximum bets can reach $2,000. Regular guests can take advantage of the Infinity Rewards loyalty program, which allows members to earn points on gaming, dining, and drinks and redeem them for complimentary meals, beverages, exclusive tournament entries, and special offers.


Casino Canberra combines gaming excitement, stylish ambiance, diverse entertainment, and real chances for substantial winnings. Before visiting, it is recommended to check the latest tournament schedules, restaurant menus, and event listings on the official casino website.

Popular Games at Casino Canberra

Casino Canberra offers guests the atmosphere of a classic casino with a focus on table games and poker. There are no poker machines here, making the gaming experience more comfortable and centered on strategy and style.


Blackjack — one of the most popular games where the goal is to reach 21 and beat the dealer. The casino offers various betting limits starting from $5, making it suitable for both beginners and experienced players.


Roulette — the legendary game with a spinning wheel that attracts players with simple rules and the chance for big wins. Bets on numbers, colors, or groups make the game dynamic and exciting.


Baccarat — an elegant game loved by fans of the “007” style. Casino Canberra offers a version with the Dragon Bonus side bet, increasing your chances of a big payout.


Ultimate Texas Hold’em — a poker variant where players compete against the dealer rather than each other. Perfect for those who want a fast-paced game with strategic elements.


Pontoon — a poker variant where players compete against the dealer rather than each other. Perfect for those who want a fast-paced game with strategic elements.


Money Wheel — a simple and thrilling game where everything depends on the spin of the wheel. A great choice for fans of quick bets.


Poker Room — a dedicated area for classic poker with regular tournaments and prize pools of up to $6,000.

Restaurants and Bars at Casino Canberra: Premium Dining Experience

Casino Canberra offers more than gaming — it delivers high-end culinary experiences. Every guest can find the perfect spot, from signature dining to stylish cocktail lounges.


Natural Nine — Modern Chinese Cuisine

The flagship restaurant with a Pop Chinese concept, blending traditional Chinese recipes with Australian ingredients. The menu features duck, noodles, dim sum, fresh seafood, and creative desserts. Available for lunch, dinner, Yum Cha, and tasting menus. Perfect for casual dining or private banquets in Room 8.


Onyx Sports Lounge — Sports and Comfort

A sports bar with large screens broadcasting UFC, AFL, NBA, and more. The menu includes classic pub-style dishes, snacks, and drinks. During Onyx Hour, enjoy special deals: cocktails for $14, beer and wine for $7.

An elegant lounge offering signature cocktails, premium wines, and champagne. Ideal for an aperitif, evening relaxation, or social gatherings. The menu includes both classic and non-alcoholic options.

items.title: Do I need to book a table or restaurant in advance?
items.answer: Yes, especially for dinners at Natural Nine, private events in Room 8, and participation in special shows. Reservations can be made online or by phone.

items.title: Can I take photos in the casino?
items.answer: Photography is allowed only in public areas (such as restaurants and bars). Taking photos in gaming areas is prohibited to protect guest privacy.

items.title: Is there parking for Casino Canberra guests?
items.answer: Yes, free parking is available for casino guests. There are also paid city parking options nearby.

items.title: Where is Casino Canberra located and how do I get there?
items.answer: The casino is located in the city center at 21 Binara Street, Canberra ACT. You can get there on foot from central hotels, by taxi, or by public transport.

items.title: Can I play at Casino Canberra without cash?
items.answer: Yes, the casino accepts debit cards and EFTPOS for purchasing chips. Credit cards are not used for gambling.
